@tomasdedic you mentioned that the socket is aliased

> (/var/run/docker.sock is symlink to /run/user/1001/podman/podman.sock)

I interpreted it that the docker client is talking to the Podman socket.  That will  use different code paths than using `podman` directly.  If that is the case, please try with `podman` as well.

 it seems that adding containers-storage transport works:
```json
    "transports": {
        "containers-storage": {
            "": [
                {
                    "type": "insecureAcceptAnything"
                }
            ]
        },
```
